{
  "original_content": "# Document Standard SFS 2487\n\nThis guide is based on the SFS 2487 standard and defines the layout, tabs and structure of multi-page documents.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Page Settings and Margins\n\n- **Top margin:** 1 cm\n- **Bottom margin:** at least 1 cm (recommended 2 cm)\n- **Left margin:** 2 cm\n- **Right margin:** at least 0.7 cm (recommended 1 cm)\n- **Standard tabs:** Tabs are placed at 23 mm intervals measured from the left edge of the form.\n    - **Tab positions (cm):** C0: 0, C1: 2.3, C2: 4.6, C3: 6.9, C4: 9.2, C5: 11.5, C6: 13.8, C7: 16.1.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Document Parts and Placement\n\nRow numbers according to the standard must be adjusted according to the number of rows in the header. Word starts row numbering from 1 after the header.\n\n### Header (Example with 6-row header)\n1. **Publisher/Sender:** Written in bold (except for private individuals). Position: C0.\n2. **Document name:** Starting with a capital letter (e.g. *Offer*, *Order*). Position: C3.\n3. **Page number:** Included only in multi-page documents in the format `PageNo (TotalPages)`, e.g. `1 (5)`. Position: C6.\n4. **Document supplement:** Clarifying information, e.g. *Certificate of Employment – Temporary*. Position: C3.\n\n### Recipient and Headings\n- **Recipient:** According to the standard, begins on row 7. If the header is 6 rows, write after the header on row 1.\n- **Reference:** Standard row 14. For example, *Your advertisement in HS on 1.11.2009*.\n- **Main heading:** Standard row 16. Written in bold.\n- **Text:** According to the standard, begins on row 20. Text is indented to tab position C2 (4.6 cm).\n\n---\n\n## 3. Dates and Information\n\n- **Date:** In domestic correspondence, use the format `day.month.year` (e.g. 4.11.2009). No leading zeros are used.\n- **Contact information:** Organization name, address (PO box/street address), phone, fax, email, website, Business ID and registered office are usually placed in the header or footer in columns according to the standard.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Closing Entries\n\nSpace is left at the end of the document for signatures and possible additional information:\n\n1. **Closing greeting:** 2 line breaks after the text.\n2. **Publisher/Sender:** 2 line breaks after the greeting, written in CAPITAL LETTERS.\n3. **Signature and name clarification:** 3–5 line breaks after the sender's name. The position/title is written below the name clarification.\n4. **Additional entries:** The words *Attachment*, *Distribution* and *CC* are written at least one row below the name clarification.\n    - Listed attachments are written with a capital first letter.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Footer\n\n- There must be at least 3 empty rows before the footer.\n- Information is usually written in a smaller font than the main text.",
